This issue is to implement the API design that I [presented at the LSST Project and Community Workshop](https://project.lsst.org/meetings/lsst2016/agenda/end-end-galsim-lsst).

Here is the proposed new structure for how `drawImage` will work (from slide 14 of my talk):
```
def drawImage(..., sky=None, surface_ops=(), sensor=None):
    ... # Various setup steps that won't need to change.
    if method == 'phot':
        photon_list = prof.SBProfile.shoot(n_photons, ...)
        if return_photon_image:
            photon_image = SimpleCCD().accumulate(photon_list, image.copy())
    else:
        prof.SBProfile.draw(image.image, ...)
        if sensor is None:
            return
        elif return_photon_image:
            photon_image = image.copy()
        ii = InterpolatedImage(image)
        photon_list = ii.SBProfile.shoot(n_photons, ...)

    photon_list.generateWavelengths(sed * bandpass)
    if sky:
        photon_list.addSkyPhotons(sky, sky_sed * bandpass)
    photon_list.shuffle()

    for surface_op in surface_ops:
        photon_list = surface_op.apply(photon_list)

    if sensor is None:
        sensor = SimpleCCD(gain, ...)
    sensor.accumulate(photon_list, image.image)
```
In this issue, the goal is to maintain current functionality, but have the above hooks in place for people to add non-trivial sensor models.

At the LSST Hack week in November, if this is all in place, we can try to merge it into branch #722 where @craiglagegit has been implementing his sensor model.  His model would be passed in as the new `sensor` parameter to `drawImage`.

